docs\progress\logs\20260626-050107_execute-P005.log:12913:I’m thinking about how to reconstruct plan-level configurations with linked intakes. If the plan is generated and then the source row configuration gets edited, it could lead to changes. I realize it’s important to maintain consistency with the CLI configuration, ensuring it doesn’t switch midway if default values change. What happens if the user changes the intake configuration after linking the plan ID? That might necessitate a snapshot to preserve the plan, but I’m hesitant about potential DB migrations. Maybe creating an event could help clarify this!
